## Phase 6 — DPDK UDP Receiver (Kernel-Bypass Endgame)  🟡 ⚠️ hardware-gated  (10 days)

> Reach only after the book is correct, measured & understood at the epoll layer.
> **Dependency risk:** needs a DPDK-compatible NIC (Intel X520/X710-class) + hugepage-capable bare-metal box
> — not achievable on a laptop. This acquisition step can slip the 7-week budget independent of coding pace.
>
> **Bare-metal re-calibration:** the moment this box is provisioned, before any DPDK-specific work, re-run
> every measurement from Phase 1 (SP 1's percentile harness, core pinning, `performance` governor — including
> the pieces explicitly deferred earlier because Docker/VM couldn't do them — and SP 2's full hardware cost
> report) natively on that hardware: no Docker, no virtualization layer. Everything measured so far ran under
> at least one layer of indirection (Docker Desktop's VM on Apple Silicon, plus the earlier caveat that even
> real cloud instances are normally KVM-virtualized unless `.metal`) — those numbers were for verifying
> mechanism/correctness only, never treated as trustworthy absolute latency figures. This re-run is what
> produces the numbers that actually go in the README/portfolio.

### SP 11 — DPDK bring-up  ⏱ 5 d
- [ ] 🟡 DPDK-compatible NIC + hugepage configuration
- [ ] 🟡 DPDK "hello world" RX
- [ ] 🔴 Re-run Phase 1 (SP 1 + SP 2) in full on this bare-metal box — governor now actually settable,
      `rdtsc` now real x86 hardware, no VM/hypervisor jitter — these become the numbers reported everywhere
- **Output:** a DPDK app printing raw captured Ethernet frames + a refreshed Phase 1 report with real
  bare-metal numbers, superseding the earlier Docker-based results.

### SP 12 — Frame capture → pipeline + final comparison  ⏱ 5 d
- [ ] 🟡 Raw Ethernet frame capture in userspace → existing ITCH/book pipeline (UDP only, no custom TCP)
- [ ] 🟡 Full 4-transport percentile graph (kernel → epoll → busy-poll → DPDK)
- [ ] 🟡 perf/VTune pass + ≥1 profiling-driven optimization, re-measured
- **Output:** the final comparison graph + a written profiling note (the capstone result artifact).

